Tottenham Hotspur midfielder, Dele Alli’s new club has finally been revealed. According to football transfer expert, Fabrizio Romano, Alli has agreed to a deal to join Everton on a permanent transfer. Romano made this known in a tweet via his Twitter handle on Monday (transfer deadline day). He tweeted, “Dele Alli to Everton, done deal and here we go! Full agreement reached with Tottenham, permanent move subject to medical in the next few hours. It’s done. “Frank Lampard wanted Dele after van de Beek – official announcement later today.” Meanwhile, Everton had signed Donny Van de Beek from Manchester United.